WEBVTT

00:16.099 --> 00:18.936
CUS:
This is all about immortality,

00:18.936 --> 00:22.606
about your name being known
till the end of time.

00:22.606 --> 00:27.236
We have to wait for our moment
like crocodiles in the mud.

00:27.236 --> 00:29.738
No one knows
when the drought will come.

00:29.738 --> 00:32.699
And the animals will have
to migrate across the Sahara.

00:32.699 --> 00:34.826
But we will be waiting.

00:34.826 --> 00:37.037
Months. Years.

00:37.037 --> 00:39.623
And the gazelles
and the wildebeests

00:39.623 --> 00:41.041
will cross the water.

00:41.041 --> 00:44.461
And when they come,
we will bite them.

00:44.461 --> 00:46.004
You hear me, son?

00:46.004 --> 00:50.384
We will bite them so hard
that when they scream,

00:50.384 --> 00:52.552
the whole world
is gonna hear them.

00:52.552 --> 00:54.721
You will supersede everyone.

00:54.721 --> 00:56.556
You are a giant.

00:56.556 --> 00:59.393
You are a colossus amongst men.

00:59.393 --> 01:01.770
If you listen...

01:01.770 --> 01:04.189
you will one day reign
like the gods.

01:04.189 --> 01:06.733
[upbeat rock music]

01:06.733 --> 01:09.027
- I didn't know what the fuck
a gazelle was.

01:09.027 --> 01:11.446
But I never heard anyone
say anything good about me.

01:11.446 --> 01:13.115
I wanted to hear more.

01:13.115 --> 01:14.533
CUS:
Boxing is entertainment.

01:14.533 --> 01:18.036
So to be successful,
a fighter must not only win,

01:18.036 --> 01:20.080
but he must win
in an exciting manner.

01:20.080 --> 01:21.915
♪ ♪

01:21.915 --> 01:23.500
SINGER:
♪ You got to ♪

01:23.500 --> 01:25.836
- He must throw punches
with bad intentions.

01:25.836 --> 01:27.462
You hear me, Mike?

01:27.462 --> 01:29.298
With the speed of the devil.

01:29.298 --> 01:30.799
Your mind is not your friend.

01:30.799 --> 01:32.301
I hope you know that, Mike.

01:32.301 --> 01:34.511
You have to fight your mind.
Control it.

01:34.511 --> 01:36.138
Block your feelings.

01:36.138 --> 01:38.807
Fatigue is 90% psychological.

01:38.807 --> 01:40.559
- Three, four, five.
CUS: To be a great fighter,

01:40.559 --> 01:42.060
you have to get out
of your head.

01:42.060 --> 01:44.104
Keep your emotions shut off.

01:44.104 --> 01:45.939
A gladiator.

01:45.939 --> 01:49.026
A gladiator
focuses on his objective

01:49.026 --> 01:50.986
and blocks everything else out.

01:50.986 --> 01:53.488
MIKE: Mind control shit?
I didn't care.

01:53.488 --> 01:56.241
I never had anyone
interested in me before.

01:56.241 --> 01:57.617
I ate that shit up.

01:57.617 --> 01:59.703
I'm the best fighter
in the world.

01:59.703 --> 02:01.705
I'd train with Cus
three times a week

02:01.705 --> 02:03.498
and go back to Tryon at night.

02:03.498 --> 02:05.584
Best fighter in the world.
No one can beat me.

02:05.584 --> 02:08.545
♪ ♪

02:08.545 --> 02:09.755
TEDDY:
We gotta talk about Mike.

02:09.755 --> 02:12.632
- For crying out loud, Teddy.

02:12.632 --> 02:14.259
He didn't steal your money.

02:14.259 --> 02:15.344
TEDDY:
He did steal my money.

02:15.344 --> 02:16.345
That's not
what we gotta talk about.

02:16.345 --> 02:18.347
- It wasn't Mike.

02:18.347 --> 02:19.765
TEDDY:
He's gonna be paroled soon.

02:19.765 --> 02:20.766
- [whispering]
It was me.

02:20.766 --> 02:22.309
CUS:
So? That's a good thing.

02:22.309 --> 02:24.061
- Back to Brooklyn, where he'll
go do something stupid

02:24.061 --> 02:26.229
and get killed,
get locked up again.

02:26.229 --> 02:27.397
- Shit.

02:31.026 --> 02:33.278
My mother always said you go
to a person's house

02:33.278 --> 02:35.238
for the first time...

02:35.238 --> 02:37.074
you bring a gift.

02:42.621 --> 02:45.207
- Those are
some cheap-ass chocolates.

02:48.043 --> 02:49.503
No, thank you.

02:50.962 --> 02:52.422
You wanna take him?

02:52.422 --> 02:53.840
- Not take.

02:55.884 --> 02:57.552
You'll see him anytime.

02:58.428 --> 03:00.055
LORNA MAE: You think
that you'll do a better job

03:00.055 --> 03:01.807
than me?

03:01.807 --> 03:04.601
He know right from wrong,
but he don't care.

03:04.601 --> 03:06.395
CUS: I'll see he stays
out of trouble.

03:06.395 --> 03:08.397
- [scoffs]

03:08.397 --> 03:10.315
I don't know how many times
they come to me

03:10.315 --> 03:12.192
telling me he's arrested.

03:12.192 --> 03:14.778
I gotta take care
of three kids

03:14.778 --> 03:16.446
without no help from anybody.

03:16.446 --> 03:17.864
CUS:
Lorna Mae,

03:17.864 --> 03:20.450
Mike's got a potential.

03:20.450 --> 03:23.078
He's got a real serious talent.

03:23.078 --> 03:25.080
I know I could bring it out
in him.

03:26.456 --> 03:28.417
- And what's in it for you?

03:28.417 --> 03:30.085
- I've been doing this
all my life.

03:30.085 --> 03:33.588
Believe me when I tell you
he could go the distance.

03:33.588 --> 03:36.216
- If he can't box no more,

03:36.216 --> 03:39.010
you still keep him?

03:40.804 --> 03:42.681
That's what I thought.

03:45.225 --> 03:47.894
What's in it for you,
motherfucker?

03:48.895 --> 03:50.939
- Well, I'll be his manager.

03:55.902 --> 03:57.654
- You rather go live with him?

04:04.953 --> 04:05.954
- Yeah.

04:14.838 --> 04:15.922
- Take him.

04:16.798 --> 04:18.675
He only gonna disappoint you.

04:29.102 --> 04:31.813
You forgot
your fucking chocolates.

04:35.859 --> 04:38.862
[mellow music]

04:38.862 --> 04:43.784
♪ ♪

04:43.784 --> 04:45.911
[children chattering]

04:45.911 --> 04:49.498
SINGER: ♪ It seems
I've abandoned my dreams ♪

04:49.498 --> 04:54.211
♪ I'm on the run,
sinkin' with the sun ♪

04:54.211 --> 04:55.921
♪ ♪

04:55.921 --> 04:57.422
♪ Lost in them pale blue eyes ♪

04:57.422 --> 04:58.590
- I don't know why you think

04:58.590 --> 05:00.467
that extra gravy's
so necessary, Mike.

05:00.467 --> 05:02.761
You're gonna spend all morning
tomorrow running it off.

05:02.761 --> 05:06.723
♪ ♪

05:06.723 --> 05:10.060
- Cus, this is
the best cheese I ever had.

05:10.060 --> 05:11.686
What kind of cheese is this?

05:11.686 --> 05:13.730
- What the fuck?

05:13.730 --> 05:15.816
You're eating butter.

05:15.816 --> 05:17.901
[laughter]

05:19.236 --> 05:21.071
- All right, all right.

05:26.576 --> 05:27.953
- It was round.

05:28.954 --> 05:31.164
I never seen round butter.

05:31.164 --> 05:33.291
- It's European.
Camille likes it.

05:35.043 --> 05:38.380
When people hear my accent...

05:38.380 --> 05:40.465
they know I'm a guy
from the streets.

05:42.133 --> 05:44.344
They underestimate me.

05:44.344 --> 05:47.138
They'll underestimate you, too,
'cause you're Black.

05:48.390 --> 05:49.808
Let 'em.

05:49.808 --> 05:51.518
We'll use it to our advantage.

05:52.811 --> 05:54.646
Here's the plan.

05:54.646 --> 05:57.691
Junior Olympics, a warm-up.

05:57.691 --> 05:59.943
Then real Olympic gold at 18.

05:59.943 --> 06:01.820
Then we turn pro,

06:01.820 --> 06:04.030
and we go for the title
and we grab it.

06:05.490 --> 06:08.034
The world championship.

06:08.034 --> 06:10.412
- Why do you think
I can be that?

06:10.412 --> 06:12.789
- Because you can.

06:12.789 --> 06:15.083
Don't you wanna change
your life?

06:15.083 --> 06:17.377
You don't even know
what European butter is.

06:18.336 --> 06:20.630
[jazzy music]
MIKE: [soft laugh]

06:20.630 --> 06:24.134
AUDIENCE: Aww!

06:24.134 --> 06:26.011
- At this point,
Cus was kind of down and out

06:26.011 --> 06:27.387
in his career.

06:27.387 --> 06:28.972
All his hopes were on me.

06:30.223 --> 06:31.892
He really needed a win.

06:31.892 --> 06:34.436
♪ ♪

06:34.436 --> 06:36.771
It's kind of a lot
for a 13-year-old.

06:36.771 --> 06:39.774
These two messed-up guys met,
and they made history.

06:39.774 --> 06:41.526
Now, Cus was kind of a--
he was kind of a quirky

06:41.526 --> 06:43.737
kind of a character
kind of guy, right?

06:43.737 --> 06:45.363
All his coat pockets
were sewn shut

06:45.363 --> 06:47.073
so nobody could plant drugs
on him.

06:48.158 --> 06:49.784
He wouldn't drink in public
because he assumed

06:49.784 --> 06:52.037
someone
would slip him a Mickey.

06:52.037 --> 06:54.205
And his room?
Off-limits.

06:54.205 --> 06:55.624
Every day, he'd slip matches
in the door

06:55.624 --> 06:57.208
to see if anyone
had been inside.

06:58.251 --> 06:59.419
He was a progressive.

06:59.419 --> 07:01.296
Loved Martin Luther King
and Che Guevara.

07:01.296 --> 07:02.714
If you wanted to get
a rise out of him,

07:02.714 --> 07:04.215
all you would have to say is...

07:04.215 --> 07:06.926
I don't see how socialism
could work.

07:06.926 --> 07:08.345
- Money's useless

07:08.345 --> 07:11.181
unless you're helping people
with it.

07:11.181 --> 07:14.184
MIKE: And don't get him
started on Ronald Reagan.

07:14.184 --> 07:18.021
- Bum, liar, snake, phony!

07:18.021 --> 07:20.607
- He refused to pay taxes
to Republican administrations.

07:20.607 --> 07:22.359
Instead he declared bankruptcy.

07:22.359 --> 07:25.028
♪ ♪

07:25.028 --> 07:27.280
And this is the guy
I had to put all my faith in.

07:27.280 --> 07:29.199
[cab's tires screech]
- Except I didn't know how

07:29.199 --> 07:30.700
to believe what Cus saw in me.

07:30.700 --> 07:32.285
I'd still go back
to see my mom.

07:32.285 --> 07:33.870
[siren whoops
in background]

07:33.870 --> 07:36.915
But I started to feel like
I didn't belong there either.

07:36.915 --> 07:39.584
Yo, man, what they
teaching you upstate?

07:39.584 --> 07:40.835
You need to share that shit.

07:40.835 --> 07:41.920
LORNA MAE:
Michael.

07:41.920 --> 07:43.588
MIKE: [whispering] Sh--

07:45.131 --> 07:47.300
You smoking drugs in my house?

07:47.300 --> 07:48.718
- Just Barkim is.

07:48.718 --> 07:49.969
LORNA MAE:
Mm-hmm.

07:49.969 --> 07:51.221
Give me that shit.

07:51.221 --> 07:52.597
I send you away to do better

07:52.597 --> 07:54.015
and come back doing drugs?

07:54.015 --> 07:55.517
Don't do drugs.

07:56.643 --> 07:58.311
I keep talking,
but you ain't listening.

07:58.311 --> 08:00.021
- I didn't do anything.
We didn't do anything.

08:00.021 --> 08:01.398
LORNA MAE: I raised my kids
better than that.

08:01.398 --> 08:03.358
All except you.

08:03.358 --> 08:04.984
Drugs are bullshit.

08:04.984 --> 08:06.027
[laughter]

08:06.027 --> 08:07.028
I don't want you to end up

08:07.028 --> 08:08.488
a pimp like your father.

08:08.488 --> 08:10.323
MIKE: Maybe I'll end up
a deacon like my father.

08:10.323 --> 08:13.451
[laughs] My father was a pimp
and a deacon.

08:13.451 --> 08:15.286
[laughter]
- You ain't never gonna be

08:15.286 --> 08:16.621
no deacon, Mike.

08:16.621 --> 08:17.872
- Never be no deacon.

08:17.872 --> 08:19.624
[laughs]

08:19.624 --> 08:21.042
- [sighs]

08:21.042 --> 08:22.961
What are those people
you living with like?

08:25.880 --> 08:27.674
Your family take you back,
you know.

08:30.552 --> 08:32.846
- I just gotta be
with that old guy.

08:34.681 --> 08:35.974
- Mm-hmm.

08:35.974 --> 08:38.685
[light music]

08:38.685 --> 08:41.855
[laughter]

08:41.855 --> 08:45.233
[indistinct chatter]

08:45.233 --> 08:47.444
CUS:
Punchers are born, not made.

08:47.444 --> 08:49.904
And you got power
in both fists, son.

08:50.780 --> 08:52.240
I'm not telling you
to make you believe

08:52.240 --> 08:53.867
you're something you're not.

08:53.867 --> 08:56.703
This is what you were born
to do.

08:56.703 --> 08:58.705
I wanna get him into a smoker.

08:58.705 --> 09:00.790
- You can't put a boy
in a smoker.

09:00.790 --> 09:02.500
- What he needs is experience.

09:02.500 --> 09:04.502
- No one's gonna fight a kid
who just turned 14.

09:04.502 --> 09:06.546
I mean, you're not gonna find
an opponent.

09:06.546 --> 09:08.298
- Of course
I'm not gonna find an opponent.

09:08.298 --> 09:10.383
You are.
That's your fucking job.

09:11.301 --> 09:13.511
Anyway, look at him.

09:13.511 --> 09:15.305
Who's gonna believe he's 14?

09:17.098 --> 09:18.850
- Cus, he's a kid.

09:18.850 --> 09:20.393
I'll get arrested.

09:20.393 --> 09:23.813
♪ ♪

09:23.813 --> 09:26.858
[crowd cheering]

09:29.194 --> 09:30.779
- Get the fuck out of here,
Teddy.

09:30.779 --> 09:32.072
You gonna look me in the eye
and tell me

09:32.072 --> 09:33.490
that this guy is 14?

09:33.490 --> 09:34.574
- Hand to God.

09:34.574 --> 09:35.867
- Where do you get the balls?

09:35.867 --> 09:36.910
TEDDY:
What do you want me to say?

09:36.910 --> 09:38.244
The kid just turned 14.

09:38.244 --> 09:40.205
- Nah, get out of my gym.

09:40.205 --> 09:41.664
- Fine.

09:41.664 --> 09:42.791
He's 18.

09:42.791 --> 09:44.084
NELSON:
There it is.

09:44.084 --> 09:45.752
You know something, Teddy?

09:45.752 --> 09:47.754
Sometimes I think you lie worse
than we do.

09:47.754 --> 09:50.757
[crowd yelling]

09:52.050 --> 09:53.510
- How you doing, Mike?

09:55.011 --> 09:56.387
- I was a baby.

09:56.387 --> 09:57.764
What I wanted to say was,
"Get me out of here.

09:57.764 --> 09:59.349
I'm a fucking kid."

09:59.349 --> 10:01.184
Instead I said...

10:01.184 --> 10:02.727
I'm gonna get something
from the grocery store

10:02.727 --> 10:04.354
down the street.

10:05.897 --> 10:07.524
- Hurry back.

10:08.733 --> 10:11.736
[car alarms blaring,
dogs barking]

10:14.239 --> 10:17.283
[child crying,
indistinct chatter]

10:17.283 --> 10:19.661
[glass shatters]

10:19.661 --> 10:23.164
[indistinct chatter]

10:30.630 --> 10:33.424
[funky music]

10:33.424 --> 10:35.343
MIKE: People went after Cus
for exposing a young kid

10:35.343 --> 10:38.096
to a place like that
and making him fight.

10:38.096 --> 10:40.682
But that filthy place--
it represented hope.

10:40.682 --> 10:42.142
It was my way out.

10:42.142 --> 10:44.352
It made me become
who I needed to become.

10:44.352 --> 10:46.938
Oh, and I knocked
that motherfucker out.

10:46.938 --> 10:48.815
SINGER:
♪ Hold on ♪

10:48.815 --> 10:50.483
♪ ♪

10:50.483 --> 10:53.653
♪ And when there's a struggle ♪

10:53.653 --> 10:55.363
♪ Hold on ♪

10:55.363 --> 10:57.657
- Yes, Michael!

10:57.657 --> 11:00.034
- I won my very first fight.

11:00.034 --> 11:02.203
Knocked that motherfucker
out cold.

11:02.203 --> 11:04.247
Whoo!

11:04.247 --> 11:05.540
Yeah!

11:05.540 --> 11:06.791
Whoo-hoo-hoo!

11:06.791 --> 11:07.959
Whoo!

11:07.959 --> 11:11.087
Yeah!
Yes, yes, whoo!

11:11.087 --> 11:13.172
That's when the legend
of Mike Tyson began.

11:13.172 --> 11:15.341
Yes!
Whoo!

11:15.341 --> 11:16.801
[yells]

11:16.801 --> 11:18.636
[breathing heavily]

11:20.889 --> 11:22.140
- The path is clear, son.

11:22.140 --> 11:24.225
Junior Olympics.

11:24.225 --> 11:25.393
A warm-up.

11:25.393 --> 11:29.105
Then real Olympic gold at 18.

11:29.105 --> 11:31.608
Uh, then we go pro...

11:31.608 --> 11:33.067
and grab the title.

11:33.067 --> 11:35.111
But I don't want you acting

11:35.111 --> 11:38.198
so [laughs] excited
when you win a fight.

11:38.198 --> 11:39.908
I want you arrogant.

11:39.908 --> 11:42.285
You act like
you're surprised you won.

11:45.413 --> 11:48.208
You crying?

11:48.208 --> 11:50.919
[laughs]
What's wrong with you?

11:50.919 --> 11:53.212
- I won't ever get bullied
no more.

11:53.212 --> 11:54.672
CUS:
No.

11:54.672 --> 11:57.884
Your superiority is...

11:57.884 --> 11:59.636
undeniable.

11:59.636 --> 12:03.222
They'll love you
as much as they fear you.

12:03.222 --> 12:07.018
But the fight starts
before you enter the ring.

12:07.018 --> 12:09.354
You gotta be
the meanest fighter

12:09.354 --> 12:10.730
God ever created.

12:10.730 --> 12:12.690
No more crying.

12:12.690 --> 12:14.817
Intimidation.

12:14.817 --> 12:17.946
You need to embrace
your villainy.

12:17.946 --> 12:19.948
[bell dings]

12:20.949 --> 12:23.910
[cheers and applause]

12:23.910 --> 12:25.787
MIKE: Junior Olympics,
I won every fight

12:25.787 --> 12:27.997
by knockouts
in the first round.

12:27.997 --> 12:30.083
I got gold in eight seconds.

12:30.083 --> 12:33.294
I was this local hero
with a gold medal at 14,

12:33.294 --> 12:36.547
and half my friends back home
were already dead.

12:36.547 --> 12:38.132
I loved Cus so much, if he
would've told me I could fly,

12:38.132 --> 12:39.509
I would've believed him.

12:39.509 --> 12:41.010
Only I kept going back
to Brownsville,

12:41.010 --> 12:43.471
getting fucked up and shit.
[laughter]

12:43.471 --> 12:45.556
Oh, you guys are gonna see me
really fucked up in this show.

12:45.556 --> 12:48.059
[laughter]

12:48.059 --> 12:50.520
You know, um...

12:50.520 --> 12:53.481
back then, I was living
in two worlds at the same time.

12:53.481 --> 12:54.983
Or I was trying to.

12:54.983 --> 12:58.111
♪ ♪

12:58.111 --> 13:00.780
I've been doing that
my whole life.

13:00.780 --> 13:05.326
♪ ♪

13:05.326 --> 13:06.869
It's the gold medal.

13:08.288 --> 13:09.664
Read this.

13:19.924 --> 13:21.592
- You Muhammad Ali now?

13:25.013 --> 13:27.140
- I'm gonna be the youngest
heavyweight champion

13:27.140 --> 13:29.183
in the world.

13:29.183 --> 13:30.643
Me.

13:32.020 --> 13:33.604
I am that someone.

13:36.858 --> 13:39.861
- I'm used to you smelling
like drink and reefer.

13:39.861 --> 13:41.696
Look at you now.

13:43.114 --> 13:46.075
[laughs]

13:46.075 --> 13:48.119
You better keep on winning.

13:48.119 --> 13:50.204
'Cause the second you lose,

13:50.204 --> 13:52.540
that man's throwing
your ass out.

13:54.333 --> 13:56.586
He don't love you.

13:56.586 --> 13:58.129
He's using you.

13:59.839 --> 14:02.091
He's got his own reasons
for teaching you.

14:06.012 --> 14:07.930
- He's teaching me
to be somebody.

14:09.724 --> 14:12.060
Opposite of what you ever did.

14:13.478 --> 14:14.854
I'm going to Barkim's.

14:16.856 --> 14:19.275
- Don't rob any houses, now,
you hear?

14:22.236 --> 14:24.322
- I don't do that shit no more.

14:25.490 --> 14:27.075
Look at me!

14:28.409 --> 14:29.744
[softly] Look.

14:31.162 --> 14:33.081
I am disciplined now.

14:33.081 --> 14:36.375
I'm not that piece of shit
you said I was anymore.

14:39.545 --> 14:41.005
I have pride.

14:48.054 --> 14:49.180
[door thuds shut]

14:49.180 --> 14:51.057
[glass shatters]

14:51.057 --> 14:52.767
BARKIM:
Aah, come on, come on.

14:52.767 --> 14:54.852
Hurry up, bitch,
before somebody sees you.

14:54.852 --> 14:56.354
Shit.

14:56.354 --> 14:57.563
TV!

14:57.563 --> 14:59.065
[laughter]

14:59.065 --> 15:00.608
